@NODE Background "Conftop: Background and Purpose"
[------------( Background and Purpose )-----------------------------------]

Conftop was orginally written becouse it didn't exists any good Conftop
utility when i needed one. I first tested Van Dammes Conftop utility, but
it was slow and i didn't get it working correctly so i started coding my
own. The first version was coded in arexx and was pretty slow, so i decided
to recode it in C which is much faster.

As the sysop you can specify the interval (number of days), how many rows,
and if you want to write a message when reseting. You may also have a
headerfile/tailerfile and a exclude-files for one or all conferences.
All this functions are explained later in this document.

Conftop can now be made resident. I really recommend you to do this, since
it will speed this door up quite much, specially on 68000-68020 computers!
@ENDNODE
@NODE Features "Conftop: Notable Features"
[------------( Notable Features )-----------------------------------------]

Several reasons to use Conference Top Uploaders:

* Written entirely in C for fast code.
* Works without conference accounting.
* Configable: Write message to optional user when reseting.
* Can be made resident.
* Can run other filecheck doors after.
* Can display header/tailer files, different ones for each conference, 
  as well as global ones for all conferences.
* Checks for private uploads.
* Special optimized versions for all CPU types.
* Online updating.
* 32-Node compatable. (Actually how many nodes you want)
* Using Icons (/X3.x Standard Nowadays), but should work fine with /X2.x
  and Sigma Express.
* Can use a global datafile for all conferences and/or seperate ones for
  individual conferences.
* Allows skipping update if specific user is named (by username or slot)

Conftop only allow one door to be started after. If this isn't enough,
i recommend you to use S-Dupecheck by Pot-Noodle or Dupecheck by Byteandi.
@ENDNODE
@NODE Install "Conftop: Install into Express"
[------------( Install into Express )-------------------------------------]

This door should be installed as your standard FileCheck door.
On /X3.x you have you have to edit (or create) the filecheck.info in
your Syscmd directory. On /X2.x and SExpress you have to edit the
SYS.Cmd in the usual way. Remember to give this door a low access level
(Like "001") and make it multinode. The door is an XIM type ofcourse!

Also, for added speed, you may make the door resident with your normal
"resident" command (CLI: "Resident Conftop.x PURE"). But if you do, make
sure that Express runs just the doorfilename, without its path. On /X3.x
you also need the tooltype RESIDENT in the icon.

You also need a icon in your bbscmd directory. Just copy your created
filecheck icon into you bbscmd dir and name it CONFTOP.INFO.
On /X2.x, just snap the line you just entered in sys.cmd and insert it
into your bbs.cmd file and rename FILECHECK to CONFTOP.
@ENDNODE
@NODE Config "Conftop: How to configurate conftop"
[------------( How to configurate conftop )-------------------------------]

While you're reading this section it may be a good idea to view the example
icons that came with the archive.

The whole way to configurate conftop is totaly changed. I am now using
icons since it is the standard nowadays. You have one icon for global
data in doors: (eg all tooltypes you want to be available for all
conferences) and you have one icon in each conference you want to run
conftop in. Read the next chapter to see available tooltypes.

The only thing you need to do to install conftop into a conference is to
create a iconfile in the specific conference path and put the tooltype
DAYS in it. (EG DAYS=7 or DAYS=WEEKLY)
@ENDNODE
@NODE Tooltypes "Conftop: Available Tooltypes"
[------------( Available Tooltypes )--------------------------------------]

Here are the available tooltypes.

[*] - Can be used both in the global and the local icon.
[-] - Can only be used in the global icon (Doors:Conftop.info)
[!] - Can only be used in the local icon (<confpath>/Conftop.info)

Tooltype-Name:                    Description:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
DAYS=<days/weekly>            [!] This tooltype specifies the interval of
                                  conftop. You can put it to WEEKLY if you
                                  want to run conftop weekly (Monday->Sunday)
                                  EG: DAYS=WEEKLY,DAYS=14

ROWS=<# rows>                 [*] This tooltype specifies how many rows/lines
                                  with users you want to display.
                                  EG: ROWS=10

MAILUSER=<username>           [*] This tooltype specifies which user you
                                  want to write a message to when conftop is
                                  reseting. If this tooltype is not specified
                                  at all, no message will be written.
                                  EG: MAILUSER=EALL

BULLFILE=<bulletinefile>      [*] This tooltype specifies where you want to
                                  write the bulletin file to when reseting.
                                  If this tooltype is not specified at all,
                                  no bulletine will be written.
                                  EG: BULLFILE=BBS:Bulletins/Bull1.txt

SHARE_DATA=<confpath>         [!] If this tooltype is specified, all other
                                  tooltypes will be disabled. This allows
                                  a conference to be run at another confs
                                  datafile/icon. Eg: SHARE_DATA=BBS:Conf1/

SHOW_RESETDATE                [*] This tooltype specifies if you want to
                                  show the complete resetdate instaid of
                                  showing eg: Day (1/7).

NEXTDOOR=<doorname>           [*] This tooltype specifies which door that
                                  should be started after conftop have run.
                                  EG: NEXTDOOR=DUPECHECK

CONFNAME=<cnfname>            [!] If this tooltype is specified, conftop
                                  will use this conference name instaid of
                                  using the one in Confconfig.info file.
                                  EG: CONFNAME=Amiga Elite

EXCLUDE_<num>=<user/slot>     [*] This tooltype specifies which users that
                                  you want to exclude from conftop.
                                  You can enter both username and slotnumber
                                  EG: EXCLUDE_1=BOBO,EXCLUDE_2=165

PLAYPEN_<node>=<dir>          [-] This tooltype is only needed if you don't
                                  have your playpen directories located in
                                  BBS:NodeX/Playpen/. If they don't, you
                                  must type your external playpen dir here.
                                  EG: PLAYPEN_1=HD2:PLAYPEN/

MIN_LIMIT=<bytes>             [*] If this tooltype is specifed, only users
                                  above the limit of <size> bytes will be
                                  displayed.

SKIP_EMPTY_LINES              [*] If this tooltype is specified, conftop will
                                  not output any empty lines. Eg if ROWS=10
                                  and only 1 user have uploaded, conftop
                                  will not fill the other 9 lines up.

FROMUSER                      [*] Here you can specify a own user the message
                                  will be written from. Default is the SYSOP.

SUBJECT                       [*] Here you can specify a own subject for the
                                  message. Default is "Results from Conftop"
@ENDNODE
@NODE History "Conftop: Program History"
[------------( Program History )------------------------------------------]

{ + }-New feature(s)         { - }-Removed feature
{ * }-changed feature        { ! }-fixed feature (Bug)
